  "prompt": "Which one is the best book of Chemistry for 12th ISC?",
  "response": "For students preparing for the 12th ISC (Indian School Certificate) examination, \"Chemistry\" by Pradeep is often recommended as one of the best reference books. Other popular choices include:\n\n1. **NCERT Chemistry Textbook for Class 12**: This is essential as it covers the ISC syllabus comprehensively and is aligned with the examination pattern.\n\n2. **Modern ABC of Chemistry** by K. S. Bhatia: This book is known for its clear explanations and extensive practice problems.\n\n3. **Physical Chemistry** by O.P. Tandon: This book is particularly useful for in-depth understanding of physical chemistry concepts.\n\n4. **Chemistry Blue Book** by A. B. Gupta: This book is tailored for ISC examination preparation and includes plenty of solved examples and practice questions.\n\nWhen choosing a book, it's important to ensure it aligns with the syllabus, provides good practice problems, and suits your learning style. Always refer to your school's prescribed textbooks and syllabus for the best guidance.",
